LEXINGTON CHENOA WIND FARM LLC RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Lexington Chenoa Wind Farm LLC ("Lexington Chenoa") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Lexington Chenoa generating facility ("Lexington Chenoa Facility").
The Lexington Chenoa Facility is a wind turbine generating facility located in McLean County, Illinois. The Lexington Chenoa Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Commonwealth Edison Company and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Lexington Chenoa's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Lexington Chenoa Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Lexington Chenoa's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Lexington Chenoa shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $550,000.00. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $45,833.33.
